[normal]4.1
[normal]              
[normal]There is much national and local Government rhetoric regarding equal access to services, ensuing equal opportuniti
[normal]es for all 
[normal]in education, employment, business development, social and health care and so on. 
[normal] But n
[normal]one of these can be addressed without proper access to transport in 
[normal]remote
[normal] areas,
[normal] where the largest 
[normal]defici
[normal]ency 
[normal]lies. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]There is no point in having the best h
[normal]ospital, factory or school if people cannot get to them and home again safely and affordably. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.2
[normal]              
[normal]Adequate
[normal] 
[normal]public and community 
[normal]t
[normal]ransport provision enables remote
[normal] communities to be
[normal]come more 
[normal]economically sustainable, reduces isolation, ensures access to
[normal] goods and services, reduces mental health problems and difficult
[normal]ies
[normal] in accessing 
[normal]medical services.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]It ensures 
[normal]access for people and businesses to earn money and contribute to the economy. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.3
[normal]              
[normal]The Inquiry is timely, in that
[normal] transportation costs will continue to rise, and existing services will continue to be threatened.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Access and mobility that urban dwellers currently take for granted are a quantum leap above that available to people is isolated communities.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Access to job
[normal]s, services, health care and a social life is critical to
[normal] both
[normal] physical 
[normal]and mental health. 
[normal] To our ageing population
[normal], isolation
[normal] is a challenge.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In some rural areas, suc
[normal]h as s
[normal]outh
[normal]w
[normal]est Wales
[normal],
[normal] younger people are moving out to find employment and older peop
[normal]le are moving in to retire
[normal].  T
[normal]he ageing of the population is accelerated
[normal], 
[normal]exacerbating the problem where car
[normal]-
[normal]less living is already least
[normal]-well
[normal] provided for.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.4
[normal]              
[normal]In many areas, there is no support for community transport from Councils.  Local groups 
[normal]seeking assistance to establish community transport have often been unable to find anyone in the Councils to engage with.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.5
[normal]              
[normal]We suspect that there may be few 
[normal]submissions to the Inquiry from local CTAs, potentially undermining the Committee’s objectives
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]We understand that very few local CTAs would have the resources available to apply to 
[normal]preparing 
[normal]a submission.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.1
[normal]              
[normal]To periodically survey
[normal] remote populations as to their mobility and access requirements, and 
[normal] 
[normal]              
[normal]community transport associ
[normal]ations for ridership, trip lengths, costs and other metrics
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.2
[normal]              
[normal]To provide a reliable source of 
[normal]additional and long-term 
[normal]grants 
[normal]to fund or part-fund 
[normal]community transport, 
[normal]with specific consideration being given to 
[normal]the items listed in Q4.4.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3
[normal]              
[normal]To 
[normal]encourage the development of best practice in the sector, by funding appropriate learning resources.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.4
[normal]              
[normal]To 
[normal]encourage all Councils to review their provisions for community transport.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.5
[normal]              
[normal]To 
[normal]regularly survey Councils as to the extent of their support 
[normal]for community transport.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Note[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]The submitting organisations propose to apply for funding
[normal]…
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]- to survey a sample of remote areas to identify typical transportation requirements
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]- to survey community transport associations
[normal],
[normal] and groups intending to e
[normal]stablish a CTA
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]              
[normal]- to survey Councils and their support for community transport
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]- 
[normal]to research and
[normal] produce a best practice manual
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]              
[normal]We would be pleased to discuss this proposal further with the Committee if requested.
